  "intent_precise": "DYNABEADS FOR IP - 96 well: Using mag_plate (deep_well_plate, slot 2), reagents (tuberack, slot 4), samples (deep_well_plate, slot 5), waste (reservoir, slot 9). With magnetic module. (1) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (2) Disengage magnets to release beads. (3) Mix 5 times at 250\u00b5L. (4) Mix 5 times at 250\u00b5L. (5) Transfer 250\u00b5L from source to destination. (6) Mix 5 times. (7) Transfer from source to destination. (8) Engage magnets at 4.2mm height for bead separation. (9) Incubate for 2 minutes. (10) Disengage magnets to release beads. (11) Mix 5 times at 250\u00b5L. (12) Transfer 250\u00b5L from source to destination. (13) Mix 5 times. (14) Transfer from source to destination. (15) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (16) Mix 10 times at 180\u00b5L. (17) Pause: 10 MINUTE GENTLE SHAKING, ROOM TEMP",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation. (volumes 50\u00b5L-250\u00b5L)",
  "intent": "For this 96-well Dynabead immunoprecipitation protocol, you'll be working with the magnetic plate in slot 2, reagents in the tube rack at slot 4, samples in the deep well plate at slot 5, and waste reservoir in slot 9. Start by transferring your sample from A1 to A1, then disengage the magnets and mix thoroughly 5 times at 250\u00b5L twice before transferring 250\u00b5L to your destination with 5 additional mixes. Next, engage the magnets at 4.2mm height and let the beads separate for 2 minutes, then disengage and mix 5 times at 250\u00b5L before another 250\u00b5L transfer with mixing. Finally, add 200\u00b5L of your binding reagent, mix 10 times at 180\u00b5L volume, then pause for 10 minutes of gentle shaking at room temperature to allow proper antibody-antigen binding.",
